 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-2: MaterializedViews fitness isomorphism is untested. The views.fitness() method (store.rs:709) claims isomorphism with compute_fitness() in bilateral.rs — the doc says 'Isomorphism invariant: this must match compute_fitness() for the same store state.' But NO test verifies this claim. The two implementations compute the same 7-component F(S) from different data sources: views.fitness() uses incrementally-accumulated counters (observe_datom one-pass), while compute_fitness() does batch computation over the full store. Three specific divergence paths exist: (1) observe_datom ignores Retract ops entirely (line 612), so spec_count, task counters, confidence_sum all include retracted datoms while batch does not. (2) The verification-depth accumulator (lines 634-643) is a no-op — depth is extracted but never stored or used, while batch computation resolves the cross-reference. (3) The task_open/task_in_progress/task_closed counters are monotonically increasing (lines 690-706), acknowledged in a comment as 'approximate — CE-4 will wire callers to use the exact computation path'. These divergences mean guidance routing uses the fast (possibly wrong) F(S) while bilateral reports use the slow (correct) F(S). The user could see F(S)=0.62 in status but F(S)=0.45 in bilateral — inconsistent numbers erode trust."
